Linux Authentication Threat Analyzer

A Bash-based Linux security monitoring tool that analyzes authentication logs and detects suspicious sudo authentication failures from /var/log/auth.log.

This project was created to practice:
Linux administration
Bash scripting
Security log analysis
Threat detection concepts
Basic SOC-style reporting

Features
Detects failed sudo authentication attempts
Extracts usernames associated with failed attempts
Counts failed attempts per user
Assigns severity levels:
MODERATE
HIGH
CRITICAL
Displays sample log entries for investigation
Command-line option support
Colorized terminal output for readability
